            .</p>
               <p>GEORGE WITT. I am <rs id="t18280911-230-viclabel1179" type="occupation">in the service of the East India Company</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-230-victim1308 t18280911-230-viclabel1179"></join>. On the 25th of July I was on the Paddington stage, opposite <placeName id="t18280911-230-crimeloc1180">Regent-crescent</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-230-crimeloc1180" type="placeName" value="Regent-crescent"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-230-crimeloc1180" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-230-off1177 t18280911-230-crimeloc1180"></join>; I felt a jerk at my pocket, looked round, and saw a boy getting down from behind the coach; I felt my pocket, and my handkerchief was gone; I saw the same boy stopped - I lost sight of him in getting down from the coach; I then saw him running, and several persons pursuing him; I think I should know him again; the handkerchief was found in the crescent, which he had passed; a girl who was drawing some children in a chaise threw it to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-230-person1309">
                  SAMUEL 
                  WITT
               <interp inst="t18280911-230-person1309" type="surname" value="WITT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-230-person1309" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-230-person1309" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with my brother on the coach on the 25th of July; he clapped his hand to his pocket, and called out Stop thief! I turned round, and saw the prisoner running away - he threw the handkerchief over the pales; I lost sight of him while I got off the coach, but I observed him enough to be certain that the prisoner is the boy.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-230-person1310">
                  RICHARD 
                  HARTLY WALL
               <interp inst="t18280911-230-person1310" type="surname" value="HARTLY WALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-230-person1310" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-230-person1310" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I produce the handkerchief, which Mr. Witt gave me; I found 1s. 6d., a knife, and a tin box on him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going home to my dinner, and running to make haste, I heard the cry of Stop thief! one gentleman was trying to get over the rails, and a girl threw the handkerchief over the rails; I know nothing of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-230-verdict1181" type="verdictDescription">
